summary: An ordinance repealing Ordinance No. 18708 entitled: "An ordinance relating to and providing for the improvement of lots 1, 2 and 3, block 194; all of block 193; all of block 188; all in Seattle Tide Lands, all in the City of Seattle,, by filling the same, and by erecting bulkheads and retaining walls thereon wherever necessary, as a sanitary measure, and fixing the established grades thereof, all in accordance with Resolution No. 1338 and Resolution No. 1381 of the city council of the City of Seattle; and providing payment therefor by the mode of "Payment in Bonds", as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle" approved June 27, 1908.
